[h1]{{LAYER_NAME}}[/h1]
[h3]Compatibility support for using {{SOURCE_MOD_NAME}} with Working Knowledge progression.[/h3]

This small layer mod connects {{SOURCE_MOD_NAME}} blocks to Working Knowledge.

For normal Steam Workshop use, add this layer mod to your world and Steam should resolve the required mods automatically after the Workshop requirements are set.

[h2]What It Does[/h2]
[list]
[*]Adds vanilla research block definitions for supported {{SOURCE_MOD_NAME}} blocks.
[*]Maps supported blocks into Working Knowledge schematic families.
[*]Lets Working Knowledge treat those blocks like normal researched/proficient technology.
[/list]

[h2]Workshop Requirements[/h2]
[list]
[*]Working Knowledge
[*]{{SOURCE_MOD_NAME}}
[/list]

[h2]Manual Or Offline Setup[/h2]
If you are copying mods locally, using offline files, or building a manual modpack, include:

[code]Working Knowledge
{{SOURCE_MOD_NAME}}
{{LAYER_NAME}}[/code]

[h2]Notes[/h2]
This mod does not include {{SOURCE_MOD_NAME}} and does not add new blocks, models, recipes, or balance rules. It is only a compatibility layer.

If {{SOURCE_MOD_NAME}} changes its block subtype IDs in a future update, this layer may need to be updated.
